At the age of 22, I was probably one of the youngest in the country to host a breakfast show which is generally hosted by very seasoned radio jockeys. So, here I was at my first job and they had given me the breakfast show and they had hugely promoted that show. I was on the hoardings in Delhi. So, that was really new for that time!
 
I feel it is very important for everyone to cherish the starting point of one’s career because those are the formative years.
There is outstanding talent in the radio industry and I was fortunate to meet and interact with them. Working in radio shaped who I’m today. 

Thank you for your love,

Maan Na Maan, Main Tera Ayushmann 

#WorldRadioDay

Imagine a world that brings forth a hope for a society where the voice of every child is heard, their questions spark curiosity, and where their challenges are met with understanding rather than judgement. More than *50% students in class 5 cannot read class 2 level text, thus resulting in them falling behind. And when they fall behind, they get labeled. The recent initiative by @pgshiksha, the flagship CSR initiative of @proctergambleIndia, shines a light on how easily we can ignore the learning gaps that exist and the profound impact those labels can have on a child’s self-esteem that extends beyond the walls of a classroom.

I want to extend my heartfelt congratulations to #PGIndia and #PGShiksha for reaching a remarkable milestone — 20 years of enabling access to quality education and positively impacting over 50 lakh children to learn and thrive through meaningful support.

*As per ASER report 2024
